{% # Validation - Preset - CTA banner v2.0.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v2.0.0 — first real Tier-3 implementation (was a stale scaffold on the old `display: block` harness). token-section is now the real production theme-root grid; the narrow banner comes from `--content-width` capping the content track; harness chrome + block labels from the shared snippets. Fixture gains a divider `separator` inside the flex group (between title and buttons) so the page actually exercises the "separator collapse in flex parents" concern this page owns — section-level separators are grid children that can't collapse; an in-flex separator is the real probe (regression-guards separator's `inline-size: 100%`). Per `validation-contract.md` Tier 3.
  - v1.0.1 — drop the per-block top-margin compensation now that block-rhythm cascade is fixed; rhythm spaces the three top-level blocks automatically
  - v1.0.0 — initial scaffold (composition reference; not tracked as a Tier-3 implementation)

  Tier-3 composition validation for the "cta-banner" pattern: a top separator, a
  centered group (title + divider + a row of two buttons), and a bottom
  separator. Exercises the cross-block cascade:

  - Separators don't collapse: the section-level separators fill the content
    track (grid), and the divider inside the flex group fills the group width
    (separator's inline-size: 100% — without it a separator collapses to 0 in a
    flex parent).
  - Nested groups: an outer column group (title + divider + button row) with an
    inner row group of two buttons; the row stacks below 40rem (container query).
  - Buttons hug their content inside the flex row (centered), not full-width —
    the button's justify-self is ignored in flex, so alignment governs.

  Button variant styling (button_style) needs Shopify GIDs in JSON, so both
  buttons render default solid-primary here; variants are exercised at
  ?view=validation--substrate--button-style.

  Reachable only at /?view=validation--preset--cta-banner.
  See `.context/docs/validation.md` + `validation-contract.md` § Tier 3.
{% endcomment %}

{% liquid
  assign color_scheme = section.settings.color_scheme | default: 'scheme-1'
  assign base_selector = 'shopify-section-' | append: section.id
%}

<token-section data-modifiers="theme-root,color-scheme:{{ color_scheme }}">
  {% render 'validation--breadcrumb' %}

  <header class="validation__intro">
    <h1>Composition: cta-banner</h1>
    <p>
      A top separator, a centered <code>group</code> (title + divider + a row of two buttons), and a bottom separator.
      Tier-3 probes that separators don't collapse — including the divider inside the flex group (the
      <code>inline-size: 100%</code> guard) — the nested row-group button layout (stacks below 40rem), and that the
      buttons hug their content in the flex row rather than filling it.
    </p>
  </header>

  {% content_for 'blocks' %}

  {% render 'validation--block-labels', section: section %}
</token-section>

{% capture dynamic_style %}
  /* Narrow banner: cap the grid content track. Inherits to token-section. */
  --content-width: 56rem;
{% endcapture %}
{% render 'utility--dynamic-style', base_selector: base_selector, css_content: dynamic_style %}
{% render 'validation--harness-styles' %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Preset: cta-banner",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "shopify-section--validation--preset--cta-banner",
  "blocks": [{ "type": "@theme" }],
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "color_scheme",
      "id": "color_scheme",
      "label": "Color scheme",
      "default": "scheme-1"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
